c.OPFO-STRIPPABLE-COMMENT.g2:a.TEXT: 11/19/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: HQ-1701269. Changed the method sc-browser-template::twm-display-screen so that the twm-displayed-on-window relation is set up before the twm-display-procedure is called when displaying an already existing browser view.
05/01/97 Ramesh Changed sc-browser-template::twm-display-screen to use API in GQSV instead of using GXL API.
04/09/97 Bug Fix: Ramesh Changed the procedure opcs-get-msg-colors so that opfom-default-priority-text-color is used as the text color for an out of range priority message.

03/13/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: Changed the method sc-browser-template::twm-display-screen so that even when the browser workspace to be displayed already exists, the twm-display-procedure of the twm-template (if any connected) gets called before showing the browser workspace.

11/21/96 Ramesh Moved the procedure twm-set-browser-filter-data from tw_mgr in to opa, since it requires scroll also.

11/20/96 Ramesh Moved tc-schematic-initialization from opa in to tc_core. Also moved the opxb-gr-client-server-toggle-buttons used by tc-schematic-initialization into telecom configuration. Thus, initializing schematic object icon-colors at start-up is not the responsibility of core fault expert. It is the users responsibility!

11/16/96 Ramesh Changed the opa-specific-initialize-window and opa-apps-specific-initialize-window procedure so that the opa-copyright display and hide is performed from opa-specific-initialize-window which is the opa twm-user-login-procedure.

Now using CH's new Fault Expert GMS menus instaed.
10/30/96 Ramesh Moved CHs new-opa-specific-initialize-window from opa_apss in to opa and replced the old opa-specific-initialize-window with this procedure renamed.

This procedure has no arguments and the users can define their own map-initialization procedure using a devu-scalar-initialization for this symbolic-parameter.
